00:18:39,515 --> 00:18:41,434
[Hocheol] Just find the fucking Santa Fe!

269
00:18:41,517 --> 00:18:42,935
Can you do it today?

270
00:18:43,686 --> 00:18:45,604
[Jinman] I thought you wanted me
to stay out of it.

271
00:18:46,021 --> 00:18:47,773
Why do you keep doing this to me?

272
00:18:49,024 --> 00:18:50,192
[Hocheol] This is the last time.

273
00:18:51,110 --> 00:18:53,279
The chairman,
he gets back tomorrow.

274
00:18:57,241 --> 00:18:59,952
Yeah, exactly.
I'm done helping you.

275
00:19:00,578 --> 00:19:03,122
If this thing goes wrong,
I'll be the one taking the fall.

276
00:19:03,205 --> 00:19:04,665
[Hocheol] I'll give you
100 more gold chips.

277
00:19:07,168 --> 00:19:08,377
[exhales sharply]

278
00:19:09,003 --> 00:19:10,671
The hell is this man talking about?

279
00:19:10,755 --> 00:19:12,923
For fuck's sake,
fucking bastard.

280
00:19:13,549 --> 00:19:14,967
What'd I just say?

281
00:19:15,551 --> 00:19:17,136
I'm not doin' it.

282
00:19:17,219 --> 00:19:20,890
[Jinman] I bet you didn't even know
Lee Dokyung escaped from the hospital,

283
00:19:20,973 --> 00:19:23,809
did you?
Detective Kang is about to call you.

284
00:19:25,811 --> 00:19:27,772
I think you're fucked now, Park.

285
00:19:28,731 --> 00:19:30,316
Think carefully, now.

286
00:19:31,984 --> 00:19:33,110
[phone beeps]

287
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:35,863
[exhales]

288
00:19:38,657 --> 00:19:40,326
This fucking asshole.

289
00:19:41,619 --> 00:19:43,204
Fuck that detective.

290
00:19:43,287 --> 00:19:44,622
Bastard.

291
00:19:45,122 --> 00:19:46,874
[exhales]

292
00:19:48,042 --> 00:19:50,169
Is Kim Heeju the only one left now?

293
00:19:50,252 --> 00:19:51,754
[coin drops in slot machine]

294
00:19:51,837 --> 00:19:53,631
[machine chiming]

295
00:19:56,592 --> 00:19:59,595
[breathing heavily]

296
00:20:13,234 --> 00:20:16,237
[blood squelching]

297
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:19,323
[banging]

298
00:20:20,241 --> 00:20:21,283
Dammit.

299
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:24,870
[distant banging]

300
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:30,960
[train whistle blows]

301
00:20:31,043 --> 00:20:34,046
[wheels clacking on rails]

302
00:20:48,477 --> 00:20:51,814
[cell phone vibrates]

303
00:20:51,897 --> 00:20:53,232
[gasps lightly]

304
00:20:53,899 --> 00:20:55,317
[vibrating continues]

305
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,572
WOOGY
INCOMING CALL

306
00:21:01,949 --> 00:21:04,493
-Yes?
-[Woogy] Hey, you fucking traitor!

307
00:21:04,577 --> 00:21:06,662
You ran off to save your own skin, huh?

308
00:21:06,745 --> 00:21:08,247
Some partner you are.

309
00:21:08,330 --> 00:21:10,583
[Heeju] You said you were gonna kill
Park Hocheol.

310
00:21:10,666 --> 00:21:12,293
Yeah, no shit!

311
00:21:13,085 --> 00:21:15,254
[Woogy] If you had just stayed there
like I said instead of running away,

312
00:21:15,337 --> 00:21:16,630
I could have killed him.

313
00:21:16,714 --> 00:21:18,215
Did Park see your face?

314
00:21:18,299 --> 00:21:19,550
[Woogy] I don't fucking know.

315
00:21:20,009 --> 00:21:21,594
It was so dark in there, I don't know.
I don't think so.

316
00:21:21,677 --> 00:21:22,803
What-what about you?

317
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:26,181
I'm not sure.
I think he might have seen me.

318
00:21:27,016 --> 00:21:28,684
Ah, dammit.

319
00:21:30,436 --> 00:21:32,354
Wait for me at the workshop, okay?

320
00:21:32,438 --> 00:21:34,940
I'll go to the office tomorrow
and see how things are going.

321
00:21:35,024 --> 00:21:36,984
-Then I'll meet up with you.
-[Heeju] No.

322
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:39,069
I told you I never want to see you again.

323
00:21:39,153 --> 00:21:41,322
[Woogy] What the fuck
are you talking about, Heeju?

324
00:21:41,405 --> 00:21:42,907
Things have changed now.

325
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:44,950
And my potatoes are still there in
the back of your car!

326
00:21:45,034 --> 00:21:46,160
I need those, you know.

327
00:21:49,538 --> 00:21:50,873
Ah, shit.

328
00:21:50,956 --> 00:21:52,333
[Woogy] Heeju, don't forget.

329
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:53,417
I'm from Yes Money.

330
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:55,210
I'll just leave it
for you at the workshop.

331
00:21:55,294 --> 00:21:56,587
Pick it up there.

332
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:57,755
Okay.

333
00:21:58,422 --> 00:22:00,674
Oh, hey, hey, hey, hey, yeah, yeah.
Heeju, Heeju.
STYLE
::cue()

334
00:22:00,758 --> 00:22:02,551
Have you heard anything from Lee Dokyung?

335
00:22:03,260 --> 00:22:05,220
I haven't. Why?

336
00:22:05,304 --> 00:22:07,932
[Woogy] Well, apparently he escaped
from the fucking hospital.

337
00:22:08,015 --> 00:22:09,767
Yes Money's looking for him, too.

338
00:22:10,976 --> 00:22:12,144
Listen.

339
00:22:13,354 --> 00:22:15,689
You need to hide the gold bars
in a better spot.

340
00:22:16,732 --> 00:22:17,900
And you better not tell anyone.

341
00:22:17,983 --> 00:22:21,445
How the hell did Cha Yujin even find out
the gold was in the mine, let alone Park?

342
00:22:22,529 --> 00:22:24,657
[Woogy] Heeju, please.
Don't trust anyone.

343
00:22:24,740 --> 00:22:26,325
How many times do I have
to fucking tell you,

344
00:22:26,408 --> 00:22:27,493
don't trust anyone?

345
00:22:27,576 --> 00:22:29,161
Especially Lee Dokyung.
Got it?

346
00:22:30,037 --> 00:22:31,246
[phone chimes and clicks]

347
00:22:32,039 --> 00:22:33,290
[inhales]

348
00:22:37,336 --> 00:22:38,712
[grunts]

349
00:22:44,426 --> 00:22:47,221
HEEJU, THIS IS DOKYUNG. I ESCAPED
FROM THE HOSPITAL. CALL ME AT THIS NUMBER.

350
00:22:57,982 --> 00:23:00,985
[cell phone vibrates]

351
00:23:02,027 --> 00:23:03,028
Hello?

352
00:23:03,821 --> 00:23:06,240
-[Heeju] Dokyung?
-Heeju, you okay?

353
00:23:08,158 --> 00:23:11,161
Yeah, I'm okay.
I'm doing fine.

354
00:23:11,245 --> 00:23:12,579
How about you? You okay?

355
00:23:12,663 --> 00:23:14,623
[Dokyung] Yeah, I'm okay.

356
00:23:14,707 --> 00:23:16,125
I'm so glad.

357
00:23:16,208 --> 00:23:18,085
I was so worried about you, Heeju.
[car horn honks]

358
00:23:18,502 --> 00:23:20,379
[Heeju] How did you get out
of the hospital?

359
00:23:21,255 --> 00:23:22,715
[Dokyung] I ran away.

360
00:23:22,798 --> 00:23:25,467
Park found out where the casket was
and I couldn't get a hold of you.

361
00:23:26,468 --> 00:23:28,470
You got my message, right?

362
00:23:29,054 --> 00:23:30,347
And you moved all the gold bars?

363
00:23:31,974 --> 00:23:34,059
Actually, maybe we should talk in person.

364
00:23:34,143 --> 00:23:35,811
Where are you now?
I can come to you.

365
00:23:35,894 --> 00:23:37,146
[inhales]

366
00:23:37,229 --> 00:23:39,189
Uh, no, I'll come to you.

367
00:23:39,273 --> 00:23:40,482
Where are you right now?

368
00:23:41,191 --> 00:23:42,401
[Dokyung] I'm still in Yangpo.

369
00:23:44,820 --> 00:23:46,071
I'll meet you there.

370
00:23:46,655 --> 00:23:49,074
Get a hotel room and then just send me
a message.

371
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:53,495
Right now it's a bit dangerous,
so I'll come by tonight.

372
00:23:56,540 --> 00:23:57,541
Okay.

373
00:23:59,793 --> 00:24:04,631
Uh, and hey,
where are the gold bars now?

374
00:24:08,969 --> 00:24:11,305
Let's meet first.
I'll tell you about it then.

375
00:24:12,306 --> 00:24:13,640
[Dokyung] Okay.

376
00:24:14,683 --> 00:24:15,684
[phone chimes and disconnects]

377
00:24:22,149 --> 00:24:23,901
[exhales]

378
00:24:24,610 --> 00:24:26,070
[Jinman] What is this?

379
00:24:31,408 --> 00:24:33,368
Ah, seriously?

380
00:24:34,036 --> 00:24:35,871
You looking to buy a car, sir?

381
00:24:36,705 --> 00:24:39,541
No, I'm here to talk to you, Heo Donggu.

382
00:24:39,625 --> 00:24:42,586
Why do you wanna talk to me?
I didn't do anything wrong.

383
00:24:42,669 --> 00:24:43,879
Yeah, yeah.

384
00:24:43,962 --> 00:24:45,547
Let's just go in the office, all right?

385
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:50,594
Oh, great. Shit.

386
00:24:50,677 --> 00:24:52,262
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
JU HARAN

387
00:24:53,347 --> 00:24:54,348
Ju Haran?

388
00:24:54,431 --> 00:24:55,557
[Jinman] Not Kim Heeju?

389
00:24:56,391 --> 00:24:57,601
Yeah.

390
00:24:57,684 --> 00:24:59,478
Why, did she cause some kind of accident?

391
00:25:00,187 --> 00:25:01,939
All I-all I did was sell her a car.

392
00:25:02,022 --> 00:25:04,942
Anything else, I don't-I don't-
I don't know anything about her.

393
00:25:07,194 --> 00:25:09,905
[Jinman] Well, it's just a little weird.
It was this woman, right?

394
00:25:12,658 --> 00:25:13,826
-Yeah.
-[Jinman] It was?

395
00:25:13,909 --> 00:25:16,120
-[Donggu] Yeah.
-Look. Different name.

396
00:25:16,203 --> 00:25:19,039
[Jinman] So it wasn't Cha Yujin.
It was Kim Heeju.

397
00:25:19,123 --> 00:25:22,167
Wait. So then are the police looking
for her,

398
00:25:22,251 --> 00:25:24,461
or is it the people from Geumseong?

399
00:25:24,545 --> 00:25:26,588
Was Park here? Park Hocheol?

400
00:25:27,131 --> 00:25:29,675
Park Hocheol?
That fucking asshole coming here?

401
00:25:29,758 --> 00:25:33,095
No way! I'd kill that fucker
if he shows his face here.

402
00:25:33,470 --> 00:25:34,471
Sure he wouldn't kill you?

403
00:25:34,555 --> 00:25:36,348
[Donggu] Hey, man, you haven't
seen me throw a punch, have you?

404
00:25:36,431 --> 00:25:39,726
I'd take him down. What,
y-you think I'm some kind of weakling?

405
00:25:39,810 --> 00:25:43,188
Punching doesn't really mean anything
when Park Hocheol pulls a knife on you.

406
00:25:43,564 --> 00:25:45,065
[Donggu] Hold on.

407
00:25:45,149 --> 00:25:48,193
If Park Hocheol is involved,
this is about Geumseong.

408
00:25:48,944 --> 00:25:51,780
Did this woman you're looking
for take something that belongs to them?

409
00:25:51,864 --> 00:25:53,699
Just call me if you see Park Hocheol.

410
00:25:53,782 --> 00:25:56,910
How many times do I have to say?
I told you he wouldn't dare.

411
00:25:57,494 --> 00:25:59,663
All right.
Look, I get it.

412
00:26:00,414 --> 00:26:03,000
You obviously don't like him at all.
Wanna kill him, right?

413
00:26:03,834 --> 00:26:06,170
Of course I do.
You see what that prick did to my ear?
STYLE
::cue()

414
00:26:07,921 --> 00:26:11,049
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

415
00:26:11,133 --> 00:26:14,136
[rustling]

416
00:26:15,762 --> 00:26:16,930
[grunts]
[gold bars clang]

417
00:26:17,431 --> 00:26:19,224
[cell phone vibrates]

418
00:26:31,236 --> 00:26:33,155
[Dokyung] Skyday, room 2014.

419
00:26:33,238 --> 00:26:35,115
You can reach me at this number
from now on.

420
00:26:54,051 --> 00:26:55,093
[elevator door dings]

421
00:27:02,017 --> 00:27:03,894
[Female Automated Voice] 23rd floor.

422
00:27:03,977 --> 00:27:05,395
Doors closing.

423
00:27:29,002 --> 00:27:30,879
[Sina] 100 ten-kilo gold bars?

424
00:27:30,963 --> 00:27:31,964
[Dokyung] Yes.

425
00:27:32,756 --> 00:27:33,757
[Sina] What's the source?

426
00:27:34,633 --> 00:27:35,634
[Dokyung] Cambodia.

427
00:27:36,301 --> 00:27:38,804
[Sina] Hold up.
Is this about the recent leak?

428
00:27:40,597 --> 00:27:41,598
Yeah.

429
00:27:43,725 --> 00:27:47,813
So, it is stolen goods.
That's bold.

430
00:27:48,438 --> 00:27:52,025
[Dokyung] Well, Interpol's lost the trace.

431
00:27:52,109 --> 00:27:55,404
No records left in any account.
It's clean.

432
00:27:55,946 --> 00:28:01,451
At the price from two years ago,
I'd say it's a win-win for both sides.

433
00:28:02,369 --> 00:28:04,329
[Sina] I would like
to see the real thing first.

434
00:28:05,956 --> 00:28:07,207
When are you coming over?

435
00:28:08,667 --> 00:28:10,002
I will let you know.

436
00:28:11,294 --> 00:28:12,295
[Sina] Okay.

437
00:28:13,463 --> 00:28:14,923
[exhales]

438
00:28:24,683 --> 00:28:29,730
WHERE ARE YOU?
ABOUT CAMBODIA...

439
00:28:29,813 --> 00:28:31,189
INCOMING VOICE CALL

440
00:28:32,024 --> 00:28:33,567
Heeju, where are you?

441
00:28:34,276 --> 00:28:36,486
[Dokyung] I just talked to the people who
are gonna buy our gold.

442
00:28:37,279 --> 00:28:39,448
We should be able to get a good price
for all the bars.

443
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:43,452
Good job, Heeju.

444
00:28:43,535 --> 00:28:44,619
It's over.

445
00:28:45,370 --> 00:28:47,706
We can just start our new lives together.

446
00:28:47,789 --> 00:28:49,249
[inhales and exhales]

447
00:28:51,334 --> 00:28:52,836
You still there?

448
00:28:52,919 --> 00:28:54,379
[Dokyung] Heeju, did you hear me?

449
00:28:55,922 --> 00:28:57,966
-I'm here.
-[Dokyung] Okay.

450
00:28:58,717 --> 00:28:59,968
You heard what I said, right?

451
00:29:01,678 --> 00:29:02,679
[inhales]

452
00:29:03,722 --> 00:29:05,640
They murdered Cha Yujin.

453
00:29:06,975 --> 00:29:08,685
[Dokyung] Yeah, I know.

454
00:29:08,769 --> 00:29:11,104
That asshole Park called
and tried to blackmail me.

455
00:29:13,231 --> 00:29:14,357
[grunts]

456
00:29:16,234 --> 00:29:17,277
But it's okay.

457
00:29:18,070 --> 00:29:19,571
[Dokyung] We've got nothing
to worry about.

458
00:29:20,363 --> 00:29:24,367
I have other contacts at airport security
so moving the gold shouldn't be a problem.

459
00:29:24,451 --> 00:29:26,536
Our Cambodian buyers said they'd help,
too.

460
00:29:27,788 --> 00:29:29,706
Cha Yujin told me everything.

461
00:29:29,790 --> 00:29:31,958
About how you two used to be together.

462
00:29:32,042 --> 00:29:33,752
[Dokyung] It didn't mean anything, Heeju.

463
00:29:33,835 --> 00:29:36,046
I don't know what she told you,
but you're different.

464
00:29:36,129 --> 00:29:37,380
It's different with us.

465
00:29:37,464 --> 00:29:39,758
Sh-she's just-she's nothing to me.

466
00:29:39,841 --> 00:29:41,635
Someone close to you just died.

467
00:29:42,719 --> 00:29:45,430
And it's okay because someone else
can help with shipping?

468
00:29:47,516 --> 00:29:48,767
[exhales]

469
00:29:50,435 --> 00:29:51,728
I guess you were right.

470
00:29:53,313 --> 00:29:55,941
Cha Yujin really meant nothing
to you at all.

471
00:29:56,024 --> 00:29:57,776
[Dokyung] That's what I was trying
to tell you.

472
00:29:57,859 --> 00:29:59,319
No one else matters.

473
00:29:59,402 --> 00:30:00,529
[exhales]
STYLE
::cue()

474
00:30:01,404 --> 00:30:02,948
You're different from all of them.

475
00:30:07,619 --> 00:30:09,121
[inhales]

476
00:30:12,874 --> 00:30:14,626
I think I've gone too far.

477
00:30:16,086 --> 00:30:18,505
[Dokyung] Where are you now?
I can come find you.

478
00:30:19,548 --> 00:30:21,299
I don't think I can see you today.

479
00:30:22,092 --> 00:30:24,469
I'm sorry. I'll call you later.

480
00:30:26,263 --> 00:30:27,264
[phone beeps]

481
00:30:28,390 --> 00:30:29,391
Wait.

482
00:30:31,935 --> 00:30:34,938
[♪ dramatic music]

483
00:31:01,464 --> 00:31:04,843
GANGWON SAEBAEK HOSPITAL

484
00:31:22,736 --> 00:31:23,987
[Heeju exhales]

485
00:31:30,869 --> 00:31:31,995
[exhales]

486
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,041
[Heeju sighs]

487
00:31:51,014 --> 00:31:52,515
[Sunok] What have you been doing?

488
00:31:55,727 --> 00:31:56,853
Auntie.

489
00:31:59,522 --> 00:32:02,025
Let me sleep here just tonight.

490
00:32:03,068 --> 00:32:05,111
[inhales and exhales]

491
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,573
I'm so tired.

492
00:32:13,453 --> 00:32:15,538
[inhales deeply]

493
00:32:15,622 --> 00:32:16,915
[Sunok] That's what it is.

494
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:20,335
You smell like a coal mine.

495
00:32:25,173 --> 00:32:27,300
That damp coal smell.

496
00:32:27,968 --> 00:32:29,177
[Sunok inhales]

497
00:32:29,261 --> 00:32:31,638
The one that miners have on their clothes.

498
00:32:45,277 --> 00:32:48,280
JEIL WORKSHOP

499
00:32:48,363 --> 00:32:51,366
[rain pattering]

500
00:33:01,209 --> 00:33:04,212
[♪ tense music]

501
00:33:11,344 --> 00:33:13,972
[door creaks]

502
00:33:24,733 --> 00:33:25,734
Hoonseok?

503
00:33:29,279 --> 00:33:30,280
You brought it.

504
00:33:33,199 --> 00:33:34,200
Yeah.

505
00:33:35,243 --> 00:33:37,537
[Woogy] And the rest of the gold bars.
[gun cocks]

506
00:33:39,497 --> 00:33:40,915
Where are they?

507
00:33:47,672 --> 00:33:49,966
[breathing heavily]

508
00:33:50,050 --> 00:33:51,176
[Woogy] Tell me.

509
00:33:52,052 --> 00:33:53,636
Where did you hide the gold bars?
STYLE
::cue()

510
00:33:55,430 --> 00:33:56,681
I'm gonna shoot.

511
00:33:58,433 --> 00:33:59,976
Three.

512
00:34:03,063 --> 00:34:04,647
[inhales sharply]

513
00:34:04,731 --> 00:34:06,024
[Woogy] Two.

514
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:08,234
One.

515
00:34:10,737 --> 00:34:11,738
[gun clicks]

516
00:34:17,077 --> 00:34:18,244
Good.

517
00:34:18,328 --> 00:34:20,205
[Woogy] Good, you got it now.
No matter what happens,

518
00:34:20,288 --> 00:34:22,665
you never tell anybody where the bars are.

519
00:34:23,625 --> 00:34:26,044
Seriously, Heeju,
if I wanted to I could've just...

520
00:34:26,878 --> 00:34:29,172
...I mean, how the hell could you
even think of betraying me like that?

521
00:34:32,217 --> 00:34:33,259
[inhales]

522
00:34:34,052 --> 00:34:35,261
[exhales]

523
00:34:40,850 --> 00:34:41,976
[Woogy] Look.

524
00:34:42,727 --> 00:34:44,270
This potato's what saved your life.

525
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:46,314
[exhales]

526
00:34:46,981 --> 00:34:48,983
So did you meet up with Lee Dokyung?

527
00:34:50,318 --> 00:34:51,403
I didn't.

528
00:34:53,154 --> 00:34:54,155
Why not?

529
00:34:55,573 --> 00:34:57,409
Because I can't trust anyone.

530
00:34:57,909 --> 00:34:59,411
Not anymore.

531
00:35:00,328 --> 00:35:01,454
Wait a sec.

532
00:35:02,997 --> 00:35:05,875
So you're not going with Lee Dokyung?
Did you end things?

533
00:35:07,794 --> 00:35:11,589
[Woogy] Yes! Good job, Heeju!
You finally got it!

534
00:35:12,298 --> 00:35:14,426
Hell, you can't trust a guy like him!

535
00:35:14,509 --> 00:35:17,303
Heh, I was trying to tell you that
this whole time, and I-

536
00:35:17,387 --> 00:35:18,388
wait a minute.

537
00:35:19,514 --> 00:35:22,100
The thing is,
you still have all the gold bars.

538
00:35:22,726 --> 00:35:24,436
[Woogy] Is Dokyung really
just gonna walk away?

539
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:27,230
Ah, shit.
Do I need to kill him?

540
00:35:27,814 --> 00:35:29,941
Don't think that I trust you, either.

541
00:35:31,735 --> 00:35:32,736
Okay.

542
00:35:34,028 --> 00:35:35,029
Be that way.

543
00:35:35,530 --> 00:35:36,531
[Woogy] You just use me.

544
00:35:37,198 --> 00:35:38,450
Keep on using me.

545
00:35:39,451 --> 00:35:40,869
As much as you want.

546
00:35:41,453 --> 00:35:42,912
[Woogy] Happy to be of service.

547
00:35:43,580 --> 00:35:47,208
For every two ten-kilo bars,
I get one one-kilo bar.

548
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:48,293
Just one.

549
00:35:48,877 --> 00:35:50,378
Not too much, right?
[chuckles]

550
00:35:51,045 --> 00:35:52,922
[Woogy] Oh, yeah. That reminds me.

551
00:35:53,298 --> 00:35:56,176
I did the math and it should take us
about six months to sell them all.

552
00:35:56,676 --> 00:35:57,677
Six.

553
00:35:58,470 --> 00:36:00,805
[inhales and exhales]

554
00:36:00,889 --> 00:36:02,348
Park knows about me now.

555
00:36:02,432 --> 00:36:04,851
That means soon your whole company will,
too.

556
00:36:04,934 --> 00:36:07,270
Not to mention the police on top of that.

557
00:36:08,813 --> 00:36:10,774
And you're telling me we have
to last six more months?

558
00:36:10,857 --> 00:36:12,984
No.
They don't know.

559
00:36:13,401 --> 00:36:15,153
[Woogy] Park? He doesn't know.

560
00:36:17,113 --> 00:36:19,282
Cha Yujin must have told Park about me.

561
00:36:19,824 --> 00:36:22,243
The gold bars, everything.
He must know.

562
00:36:25,038 --> 00:36:26,664
If Park had known it was you,

563
00:36:26,748 --> 00:36:28,583
he wouldn't have gone to the mine.

564
00:36:28,958 --> 00:36:30,668
He would have gone to the pawnshop.

565
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:35,089
So now here's the real question.

566
00:36:35,173 --> 00:36:36,216
[grunts]

567
00:36:37,467 --> 00:36:40,345
Park was alone. Why?

568
00:36:40,845 --> 00:36:42,555
After he killed Cha Yujin,

569
00:36:42,639 --> 00:36:45,016
he went to the mine alone
without telling anyone.

570
00:36:45,099 --> 00:36:46,100
[Woogy] Why did he do that?

571
00:36:49,020 --> 00:36:50,188
Because that way...

572
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:54,943
-...he could keep all the gold.
-Bingo.

573
00:36:55,568 --> 00:36:57,278
And he didn't want Chairman Ahn
to find out.

574
00:36:57,362 --> 00:36:58,404
Chairman Ahn?

575
00:36:59,948 --> 00:37:00,949
The real owner of the gold.

576
00:37:03,743 --> 00:37:06,162
Geumseong's chair,
Ahn Gyuseok.

577
00:37:07,247 --> 00:37:09,624
[Woogy] Chairman Ahn gets back
to Korea today.

578
00:37:11,334 --> 00:37:13,044
And that means Park is fucked.

579
00:37:14,212 --> 00:37:15,213
Welcome back, Chairman.

580
00:37:15,296 --> 00:37:16,631
[All] Welcome back, sir!

581
00:37:17,382 --> 00:37:20,593
[Gyuseok] These are our partners
from Cambodia. Our executives.

582
00:37:20,677 --> 00:37:22,136
-Introduce yourselves.
-Yes, sir.

583
00:37:22,220 --> 00:37:24,430
-Director Jo.
-Thank you for coming all this way.

584
00:37:24,514 --> 00:37:26,224
These guys here, take care of 'em.

585
00:37:26,307 --> 00:37:27,767
-Nice to meet you.
-Give them anything they want.

586
00:37:27,851 --> 00:37:29,686
-You understand? Only the best.
-Of course, sir.

587
00:37:29,769 --> 00:37:31,020
[Jo] This way, please.

588
00:37:33,731 --> 00:37:34,941
-Come here.
-Sir.

589
00:37:35,024 --> 00:37:36,067
What is this?

590
00:37:37,026 --> 00:37:38,111
Be more subtle.

591
00:37:39,237 --> 00:37:40,864
Apologies.
STYLE
::cue()

592
00:37:45,076 --> 00:37:48,079
[birds chirping]

593
00:37:52,917 --> 00:37:54,127
Hey, step on it.

594
00:37:54,627 --> 00:37:58,131
My stomach is starting to hurt
from all that greasy food I had to eat.

595
00:37:59,007 --> 00:38:00,133
[exhales]

596
00:38:04,429 --> 00:38:06,598
Do I really have to ask about it?

597
00:38:07,473 --> 00:38:08,766
Right, yes.

598
00:38:10,935 --> 00:38:13,688
-So, Lee Dokyung, he-
-Managed to escape from the hospital.

599
00:38:16,649 --> 00:38:18,109
You're kidding, right?

600
00:38:18,192 --> 00:38:20,236
Why did I have to hear that
from someone else?

601
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:21,905
It seemed like you had a busy schedule,

602
00:38:21,988 --> 00:38:24,741
so I was planning to report it
to you when you got back.

603
00:38:24,824 --> 00:38:27,076
You do not make decisions for me.

604
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:28,536
Yes, sir.

605
00:38:30,496 --> 00:38:31,581
So the casket.

606
00:38:32,123 --> 00:38:34,500
Is it waiting for us at the hotel?

607
00:38:35,793 --> 00:38:37,337
I'm sorry, sir.

608
00:38:38,546 --> 00:38:40,882
Enough with the apologizing
"I'm sorry" shit.

609
00:38:43,009 --> 00:38:45,136
You should know me better
than anyone else by now.

610
00:38:46,262 --> 00:38:48,765
Have I ever said anything about all
the bullshit,

611
00:38:48,848 --> 00:38:51,309
or the way you all stab each other in
the back?

612
00:38:51,851 --> 00:38:54,228
There's only one thing I can't forgive.

613
00:38:54,312 --> 00:38:57,398
And that's any damage to the company.
I will not let that happen.

614
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,652
I take responsibility.

615
00:39:02,195 --> 00:39:03,529
I'll find the casket, sir.

616
00:39:06,157 --> 00:39:07,408
It's too late now.

617
00:39:13,539 --> 00:39:16,542
[♪ suspenseful music]

618
00:39:21,005 --> 00:39:24,467
H.S HOTEL &amp; RESORT CONSTRUCTION

619
00:39:24,550 --> 00:39:26,302
[groans]

620
00:39:29,555 --> 00:39:31,683
[groaning]

621
00:39:42,527 --> 00:39:45,738
[Gyuseok] Huh, you know, maybe we dug
a little too deep.

622
00:39:45,822 --> 00:39:46,948
[grunts]

623
00:39:47,031 --> 00:39:48,199
Hey, Park Hocheol.

624
00:39:50,368 --> 00:39:53,079
[Gyuseok] Look where you are.
Shit.

625
00:39:53,162 --> 00:39:54,539
Think carefully, now.

626
00:39:56,499 --> 00:39:58,835
How did you know what was in the casket?

627
00:39:59,377 --> 00:40:00,962
Kim Jinman, he...

628
00:40:01,921 --> 00:40:03,172
...he told me.

629
00:40:03,881 --> 00:40:05,133
Ah.

630
00:40:05,216 --> 00:40:07,760
So the police already found out about it.

631
00:40:08,928 --> 00:40:10,972
And you decided not to tell me.

632
00:40:11,556 --> 00:40:13,016
You didn't bring it up.

633
00:40:13,433 --> 00:40:14,434
So that meant-

634
00:40:14,517 --> 00:40:16,811
[coughing]

635
00:40:16,894 --> 00:40:18,646
[gagging]

636
00:40:18,730 --> 00:40:20,857
So that meant I couldn't-

637
00:40:20,940 --> 00:40:22,108
I couldn't tell you.

638
00:40:22,191 --> 00:40:24,068
[gagging]

639
00:40:24,152 --> 00:40:26,279
[Gyuseok] That's not the reason.

640
00:40:26,362 --> 00:40:29,532
Otherwise, you would have
just asked me about it.

641
00:40:31,367 --> 00:40:33,786
[Gyuseok] Were you planning to find it
and take it for yourself?

642
00:40:33,870 --> 00:40:35,329
[splattering]

643
00:40:35,413 --> 00:40:37,915
[Gyuseok] Or did you already do it,
and now you're lying?

644
00:40:38,249 --> 00:40:40,084
Did you plan this with Lee Dokyung?

645
00:40:41,252 --> 00:40:43,129
No. No, sir.

646
00:40:43,212 --> 00:40:44,422
[Gyuseok] Right.

647
00:40:44,505 --> 00:40:46,841
Because if you had,
you wouldn't still be in Geumseong.

648
00:40:47,425 --> 00:40:50,386
[grunting]

649
00:40:51,804 --> 00:40:53,931
You probably would have fled already.

650
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,518
[Gyuseok] Stay out of the business
with the casket.

651
00:40:58,728 --> 00:41:01,731
Go back to Yes Money
and keep doing what you used to do.
STYLE
::cue()

652
00:41:03,274 --> 00:41:05,693
[Gyuseok] Say hi to the shareholders
at Gold Land.

653
00:41:05,777 --> 00:41:07,487
Get 'em to sign that contract.

654
00:41:08,988 --> 00:41:12,825
Yeah, the more I think about it,
it's all you're really cut out for.

655
00:41:12,909 --> 00:41:14,994
[Hocheol breathing erratically]

656
00:41:15,078 --> 00:41:16,287
Get him out.

657
00:41:18,164 --> 00:41:21,667
Fuck, I must be getting old now.
I'm getting a bit soft, huh?

658
00:41:24,879 --> 00:41:26,589
[Woojin] You know what?
[lighter clicks]

659
00:41:27,507 --> 00:41:29,717
You should have reported
this whole thing right away.

660
00:41:29,801 --> 00:41:32,261
Coulda avoided the Chairman's wrath.

661
00:41:34,013 --> 00:41:35,515
[inhales]

662
00:41:36,015 --> 00:41:38,017
You got pretty lucky in the end, though.

663
00:41:38,434 --> 00:41:40,311
[Woojin] I mean, he wanted
to cut your ear off.

664
00:41:40,394 --> 00:41:41,813
I barely talked him out of it.

665
00:41:42,855 --> 00:41:44,899
Mm, from now on,

666
00:41:44,982 --> 00:41:47,401
you should keep your head down
at Yes Money. Gimmie that.

667
00:41:48,111 --> 00:41:50,738
I'll take care of the gold bars, okay?
Here.

668
00:41:51,239 --> 00:41:52,406
Come on, Park.

669
00:41:53,449 --> 00:41:55,618
How did you know about the gold bars?

670
00:41:56,619 --> 00:41:58,663
I was in Yangpo then, wasn't I?

671
00:41:58,746 --> 00:42:00,289
[laughs]

672
00:42:00,373 --> 00:42:02,625
I sent the casket.
I've always known.

673
00:42:03,292 --> 00:42:06,796
[Woojin] You've lost your fucking touch,
you know know that?

674
00:42:06,879 --> 00:42:08,965
[Woojin inhales on cigarette]

675
00:42:09,048 --> 00:42:10,675
You don't know your place.

676
00:42:11,634 --> 00:42:13,136
Hey, here you go.

677
00:42:13,219 --> 00:42:14,470
[shovel clanging]

678
00:42:14,554 --> 00:42:15,847
Good luck getting out of there!

679
00:42:16,681 --> 00:42:18,182
[car doors closing]

680
00:42:18,266 --> 00:42:21,269
[engines revving]

681
00:42:37,785 --> 00:42:39,203
[grunts]

682
00:42:41,372 --> 00:42:44,375
[grunting]

683
00:42:44,458 --> 00:42:46,544
[breathing heavily]

684
00:43:06,397 --> 00:43:09,400
[blowtorch roaring]

685
00:43:09,483 --> 00:43:11,235
[Heeju] Park isn't the only one.

686
00:43:11,736 --> 00:43:13,613
I think someone else saw me, too.

687
00:43:13,696 --> 00:43:15,239
What do you mean?
Who saw you?

688
00:43:16,532 --> 00:43:17,533
Kim Jinman.

689
00:43:19,160 --> 00:43:21,704
I think he saw me getting
into my car that night.

690
00:43:22,955 --> 00:43:26,167
When I was running away from
the Jeongsan nightclub with Cha Yujin.

691
00:43:26,250 --> 00:43:27,919
Listen to me! Open the door!

692
00:43:28,002 --> 00:43:30,129
Look, look, look!
Roll, roll, roll down your window!

693
00:43:30,213 --> 00:43:32,548
He must not have seen you
'cause he would have reported you

694
00:43:32,632 --> 00:43:34,050
to my company right away.

695
00:43:35,092 --> 00:43:36,385
Yeah, but you know...

696
00:43:37,261 --> 00:43:40,306
...what if he's not saying anything
because he wants the gold for himself?

697
00:43:40,389 --> 00:43:42,308
Park never said anything, either.

698
00:43:42,391 --> 00:43:44,018
Ah, shit.

699
00:43:46,854 --> 00:43:47,855
Heeju.

700
00:43:48,522 --> 00:43:51,400
Your old phone and credit card.
You threw those away, right?

701
00:43:53,986 --> 00:43:55,613
Then you got no choice.

702
00:43:57,615 --> 00:43:59,742
You have to be Ju Haran
for the rest of your life.

703
00:44:00,409 --> 00:44:02,453
[exhales sharply]

704
00:44:02,536 --> 00:44:04,330
Don't worry about it.

705
00:44:05,373 --> 00:44:06,832
If Detective Kim finds out...

706
00:44:07,583 --> 00:44:09,293
...then I'll simply go
and kill him for you.

707
00:44:10,795 --> 00:44:12,463
[Woogy] Then you can give me
an extra potato.

708
00:44:14,507 --> 00:44:15,508
Deal?
STYLE
::cue()

709
00:44:19,470 --> 00:44:20,471
[Jinman] Hello.

710
00:44:20,554 --> 00:44:23,557
[distant sirens blaring]

711
00:44:28,980 --> 00:44:30,690
Hi, there. Hey.

712
00:44:31,357 --> 00:44:33,150
Uh, room five.

713
00:44:33,234 --> 00:44:35,194
Was Yeo Sunok discharged already?

714
00:44:35,278 --> 00:44:37,905
Uh, no. She was moved
to a private room.

715
00:44:38,531 --> 00:44:39,699
-She was?
-[Female Nurse] Yes.

716
00:44:41,951 --> 00:44:43,411
[Mija] Wow, so pretty!

717
00:44:44,161 --> 00:44:45,663
[Mija laughs]
[door slides open]

718
00:44:45,746 --> 00:44:47,331
Now, here.

719
00:44:47,415 --> 00:44:48,582
[Mija] Ah!

720
00:44:48,666 --> 00:44:51,460
Oh, wow.
What a nice room you got here.

721
00:44:51,544 --> 00:44:52,586
-Huh?
-[Mija] Sorry, who-

722
00:44:52,670 --> 00:44:54,839
-[Jinman] Must be pretty expensive.
-[Mija] Who are you?

723
00:44:55,172 --> 00:44:56,173
[Both] Oh.

724
00:44:56,257 --> 00:44:57,383
Is he from the ER?

725
00:44:57,883 --> 00:45:00,386
-Could you just give us a second?
-[Mija] Hmm?

726
00:45:02,096 --> 00:45:03,097
Oh.

727
00:45:06,225 --> 00:45:09,729
[Jinman] This really is a nice room.
Wow.

728
00:45:09,812 --> 00:45:10,980
[Jinman clears throat]

729
00:45:11,063 --> 00:45:13,649
[Jinman] When were you put in here?
Damn, look at this view.

730
00:45:14,358 --> 00:45:15,943
Isn't it too expensive, though?

731
00:45:16,444 --> 00:45:17,528
Why are you here?

732
00:45:17,611 --> 00:45:19,530
Just wanted to say hi
to an old friend.

733
00:45:19,613 --> 00:45:20,740
Can't a guy do that?

734
00:45:20,823 --> 00:45:23,743
Who knows?
We might not have much time left.

735
00:45:24,577 --> 00:45:26,662
I'm not just talkin' about you.

736
00:45:26,746 --> 00:45:30,333
I mean, at our age, who doesn't have some
kind of illness or some other kinda shit?

737
00:45:30,416 --> 00:45:32,126
I got diabetes.

738
00:45:32,209 --> 00:45:33,794
[Jinman] And my liver's not great, either.

739
00:45:33,878 --> 00:45:36,213
I could go any day now, you know?

740
00:45:36,297 --> 00:45:38,341
[inhales and exhales sharply]

741
00:45:39,592 --> 00:45:40,801
Hey.

742
00:45:40,885 --> 00:45:42,595
Isn't it weird we both live in Jeongsan

743
00:45:42,678 --> 00:45:44,764
but we've never run
into each other before now?

744
00:45:44,847 --> 00:45:46,891
[Sunok] More like we pretended not to.

745
00:45:47,641 --> 00:45:49,685
I saw you a couple times.

746
00:45:49,769 --> 00:45:50,936
Why didn't you say anything?

747
00:45:51,687 --> 00:45:52,938
[scoffs]

748
00:45:53,022 --> 00:45:54,482
What's the point in that?

749
00:45:55,399 --> 00:45:57,234
There's nothing left between us.

750
00:45:57,318 --> 00:45:58,319
[scoffs]

751
00:45:58,944 --> 00:45:59,945
[clears throat]

752
00:46:00,446 --> 00:46:01,447
And your husband?

753
00:46:02,239 --> 00:46:03,366
[Jinman] Has he come to see you?

754
00:46:04,492 --> 00:46:06,035
No, he hasn't.

755
00:46:06,994 --> 00:46:09,080
Well, still, doesn't seem like
he's that bad of a guy.

756
00:46:09,163 --> 00:46:10,498
I mean, he even dropped the charges..

757
00:46:12,041 --> 00:46:13,209
[inhales]

758
00:46:13,292 --> 00:46:15,669
If you're done saying hi,
you should just go.

759
00:46:16,379 --> 00:46:19,382
Instead of hanging around here,
dredging up old memories.

760
00:46:19,465 --> 00:46:21,550
Ah, come on, now.
Don't be like that.

761
00:46:23,552 --> 00:46:25,137
Oh, by the way.
Who is Ju Haran?

762
00:46:25,930 --> 00:46:28,641
I asked at the front desk
and the receptionist said Ju Haran

763
00:46:28,724 --> 00:46:30,810
is your guardian,
but I thought it'd be Han Cheoljung.

764
00:46:31,727 --> 00:46:32,728
I don't know.

765
00:46:32,812 --> 00:46:34,271
What do you mean?
It's your guardian.

766
00:46:34,355 --> 00:46:35,731
Don't tell me you don't know.

767
00:46:37,983 --> 00:46:39,193
Here, wait.

768
00:46:40,486 --> 00:46:41,487
Look at this.

769
00:46:42,363 --> 00:46:43,364
[Jinman] It's her.

770
00:46:44,031 --> 00:46:45,116
Yeah.

771
00:46:45,825 --> 00:46:46,826
Right?

772
00:46:47,868 --> 00:46:49,829
Must be. Yeah.

773
00:46:49,912 --> 00:46:52,706
I remember seeing her here the other day
when I came to visit you.

774
00:46:53,666 --> 00:46:54,959
[Jinman] It is her, right?

775
00:46:55,042 --> 00:46:56,377
[inhales]

776
00:46:56,460 --> 00:46:57,753
But then I thought,

777
00:46:57,837 --> 00:47:01,006
"This woman's name is Kim Heeju, right?"

778
00:47:01,632 --> 00:47:02,675
Who is she?

779
00:47:02,758 --> 00:47:03,801
Your daughter?

780
00:47:04,885 --> 00:47:05,886
No.

781
00:47:06,345 --> 00:47:07,596
My niece.

782
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:08,722
Your niece?

783
00:47:09,473 --> 00:47:11,308
I didn't know that you had a niece.

784
00:47:11,851 --> 00:47:14,061
-I do.
-[Jinman] I see.

785
00:47:14,645 --> 00:47:18,107
Oh, so then your niece,
she must be pretty well-off, right?

786
00:47:19,066 --> 00:47:20,401
She got you into this fancy room

787
00:47:20,484 --> 00:47:21,777
and already took care
of your hospital bills.

788
00:47:23,237 --> 00:47:24,530
[Jinman] Where does she live?

789
00:47:24,613 --> 00:47:25,906
Jeongsan?

790
00:47:25,990 --> 00:47:27,408
When is she back?

791
00:47:28,367 --> 00:47:29,368
I don't know.

792
00:47:30,661 --> 00:47:33,080
She stopped by when she heard I was sick.

793
00:47:33,789 --> 00:47:34,874
Why do you ask?

794
00:47:35,916 --> 00:47:38,669
Why do you wanna know when she'll be here?

795
00:47:38,752 --> 00:47:41,213
Well, you told me she's your niece,
so I'd like to meet her.

796
00:47:42,047 --> 00:47:43,340
What? Why?

797
00:47:43,924 --> 00:47:45,593
Has she been gambling or something?

798
00:47:46,093 --> 00:47:47,303
Is she in trouble?

799
00:47:47,386 --> 00:47:48,387
No.

800
00:47:49,180 --> 00:47:50,389
[Sunok] Then...

801
00:47:51,056 --> 00:47:53,309
...did she murder someone
or anything like that?

802
00:47:53,726 --> 00:47:56,312
Come on.
What an awful thing to say.

803
00:47:56,395 --> 00:47:57,771
Nothing like that.

804
00:47:57,855 --> 00:47:59,732
[Jinman] No, she just borrowed some money.

805
00:48:00,733 --> 00:48:02,318
-How much was it?
-[Jinman] A lot.

806
00:48:02,401 --> 00:48:03,903
Actually...

807
00:48:04,695 --> 00:48:06,280
...it's not just about the money.

808
00:48:07,072 --> 00:48:09,742
Though I'd hate for someone her age
to end up with a criminal record.

809
00:48:10,201 --> 00:48:11,994
[Jinman] It's not too late for her
to pay it back.

810
00:48:12,077 --> 00:48:13,996
Or if that's not possible,

811
00:48:14,079 --> 00:48:16,332
then she could try and reach some kind
of settlement at least.

812
00:48:16,415 --> 00:48:19,376
Looks like she turned off her phone,
and disappeared instead.

813
00:48:20,503 --> 00:48:21,670
[Jinman] That's why I brought her up.

814
00:48:22,171 --> 00:48:24,423
So if she calls you or comes to visit,

815
00:48:24,507 --> 00:48:26,008
please be sure to let me know.

816
00:48:26,634 --> 00:48:28,636
I'll be more than happy
to help her settle the matter.

817
00:48:28,719 --> 00:48:29,845
[Jinman] All right?

818
00:48:30,387 --> 00:48:31,722
Don't tell her I was here, though.

819
00:48:31,805 --> 00:48:34,225
If she knows the police are involved,
she won't show up.

820
00:48:37,645 --> 00:48:41,273
There's nothing to worry about, hmm?
I won't do anything to your niece.

821
00:48:41,732 --> 00:48:44,443
-[Jinman] Call me, okay?
-[Female Nurse] Ms. Yeo Sunok?

822
00:48:44,527 --> 00:48:46,028
I need to check your temperature.

823
00:48:46,987 --> 00:48:47,988
[clears throat]
STYLE
::cue()

824
00:48:49,198 --> 00:48:50,199
Huh?

825
00:48:54,495 --> 00:48:57,206
All right.
I'll head out now.

826
00:48:57,289 --> 00:48:59,083
You'll give me a call, right?

827
00:49:00,042 --> 00:49:01,043
Yeah.

828
00:49:01,585 --> 00:49:02,753
[machine beeping]

829
00:49:02,836 --> 00:49:04,797
[Jinman] Take care of yourself.
Get some rest.

830
00:49:08,801 --> 00:49:11,095
[exhales]

831
00:49:11,178 --> 00:49:15,099
[JEIL WORKSHOP]

832
00:49:15,182 --> 00:49:18,185
[♪ dramatic music]

833
00:49:30,990 --> 00:49:31,991
[exhales]

834
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:34,201
[light clicks on]

835
00:49:50,384 --> 00:49:51,719
[exhales sharply]

836
00:49:55,598 --> 00:49:56,599
[phone chimes]

837
00:49:56,682 --> 00:49:59,685
[phone trilling]

838
00:49:59,768 --> 00:50:00,769
[receiver clicks]

839
00:50:01,604 --> 00:50:03,230
[Dokyung] Hey, Heeju.
Where are you?

840
00:50:06,317 --> 00:50:07,860
-Uh, Dokyung-
-[Dokyung] Tell me where you are

841
00:50:07,943 --> 00:50:09,445
and I'll come find you
so we can talk.

842
00:50:17,578 --> 00:50:19,413
I'm not really sure that's a good idea.

843
00:50:19,496 --> 00:50:20,497
[sniffs]

844
00:50:21,999 --> 00:50:24,585
Do you think we can go back
to how things used to be?

845
00:50:25,586 --> 00:50:26,712
[Dokyung] What do you mean?

846
00:50:27,963 --> 00:50:30,132
Is it-is this because
of the whole Cha Yujin thing

847
00:50:30,215 --> 00:50:31,675
because I never told you about her?

848
00:50:33,218 --> 00:50:34,219
[exhales]

849
00:50:36,263 --> 00:50:37,890
You're right.

850
00:50:37,973 --> 00:50:40,351
I took advantage of a woman I was dating,
but Heeju...

851
00:50:41,226 --> 00:50:42,603
...it's different with us.

852
00:50:44,188 --> 00:50:45,356
[Heeju] I think that...

853
00:50:46,357 --> 00:50:49,109
...I was actually
the one taking advantage of you.

854
00:50:49,902 --> 00:50:50,903
When we first met...

855
00:50:51,862 --> 00:50:53,864
...I saw you as my only way out.

856
00:50:55,115 --> 00:50:58,202
No, Heeju, it's okay.
We can be happy like before.

857
00:50:58,285 --> 00:51:00,954
That money will fix everything.
What more could we need?

858
00:51:04,500 --> 00:51:05,751
Yangpo is out.

859
00:51:06,335 --> 00:51:08,379
They've tightened up security.
It's too risky.

860
00:51:09,755 --> 00:51:12,424
So I was thinking
a boat might be our best bet.

861
00:51:13,634 --> 00:51:14,760
[Dokyung] We stowaway?

862
00:51:15,386 --> 00:51:16,387
Mm-hmm.

863
00:51:17,346 --> 00:51:20,599
[Heeju] I know someone who uses
cargo ships to export cars.

864
00:51:22,267 --> 00:51:23,644
How do you know them?

865
00:51:25,688 --> 00:51:27,523
Turns out money can do anything.

866
00:51:28,023 --> 00:51:30,693
[Dokyung] Okay, then.
Let's move as quickly as possible.

867
00:51:31,193 --> 00:51:33,320
[Heeju] No, I'm not going with you.

868
00:51:33,862 --> 00:51:35,114
You're going by yourself.

869
00:51:35,698 --> 00:51:37,491
And the gold bars...

870
00:51:39,326 --> 00:51:40,536
...we should split them.

871
00:51:41,120 --> 00:51:42,121
[Dokyung] What?

872
00:51:42,788 --> 00:51:43,789
I...

873
00:51:44,707 --> 00:51:47,167
I think I deserve at least that much.
Don't you?

874
00:51:47,251 --> 00:51:50,462
I risked my life to keep them hidden.
So here's what we'll do.

875
00:51:51,088 --> 00:51:55,134
On the day you head for Cambodia,
I'll bring your share by car.

876
00:51:55,217 --> 00:51:56,927
[Heeju] I'll bring your passport, too.

877
00:51:57,010 --> 00:51:58,887
So you can just meet me at the port.

878
00:52:00,723 --> 00:52:02,975
And you won't try and find the rest
of the gold bars.

879
00:52:03,058 --> 00:52:05,185
[Dokyung] What? Heeju.
What are you talking about?

880
00:52:05,269 --> 00:52:07,312
Look, tell me where you are.

881
00:52:07,396 --> 00:52:08,772
Can we please just talk about this
in person?

882
00:52:09,523 --> 00:52:10,607
Whatever you say.

883
00:52:11,150 --> 00:52:13,402
We can just split the gold bars,
if that's what you want.

884
00:52:13,485 --> 00:52:15,154
But can we at least talk in person?

885
00:52:15,696 --> 00:52:16,822
[Dokyung] Where are you now?

886
00:52:16,905 --> 00:52:18,365
Are you still staying at the pawnshop?

887
00:52:18,449 --> 00:52:20,367
No, I'm not there anymore.

888
00:52:20,993 --> 00:52:22,119
Don't go there.

889
00:52:22,703 --> 00:52:24,663
And don't come looking for me, either.

890
00:52:25,289 --> 00:52:26,290
[phone chimes]

891
00:52:27,207 --> 00:52:28,876
Wait, Hee-Heeju.
[phone chimes and disconnects]

892
00:52:31,754 --> 00:52:34,506
[cell phone vibrating]

893
00:52:34,590 --> 00:52:35,591
[exhales sharply]

894
00:52:35,674 --> 00:52:38,093
INCOMING CALL

895
00:52:44,558 --> 00:52:46,018
POWER OFF

896
00:52:46,101 --> 00:52:47,102
[Heeju exhales]
[phone chimes]

897
00:52:52,858 --> 00:52:54,193
[sighs]

898
00:52:59,198 --> 00:53:00,324
[phone chimes]

899
00:53:00,407 --> 00:53:03,160
[Female Operator] Your call has been
forwarded to an automated voice-

900
00:53:03,243 --> 00:53:05,329
[phone chiming]

901
00:53:06,038 --> 00:53:08,373
Fuck! Why are you doing this?

902
00:53:08,457 --> 00:53:11,084
[breathing heavily]

903
00:53:11,168 --> 00:53:12,461
[groans]

904
00:53:13,045 --> 00:53:14,505
[exhales]
STYLE
::cue()

905
00:53:19,718 --> 00:53:22,721
[car approaching]

906
00:53:26,266 --> 00:53:27,768
[Hoonseok] Boss.

907
00:53:27,851 --> 00:53:29,311
I want to repay you for everything.

908
00:53:30,103 --> 00:53:33,857
I know this isn't anything special,
but I made it for you.

909
00:53:34,358 --> 00:53:35,359
Here.

910
00:53:37,277 --> 00:53:39,613
It's a four-leaf clover.
It brings good luck.

911
00:53:41,240 --> 00:53:44,785
So if you wear it then you'll be lucky.

912
00:53:46,954 --> 00:53:49,581
Oh, I made it with my own share
of the potatoes,

913
00:53:49,665 --> 00:53:51,625
so you don't have to worry about that.

914
00:53:53,335 --> 00:53:54,503
Is that true?

915
00:53:54,586 --> 00:53:55,587
What?

916
00:53:56,547 --> 00:53:57,798
[Heeju] If I keep this with me...

917
00:53:59,758 --> 00:54:02,219
...will it really bring good luck,
even to me?

918
00:54:02,803 --> 00:54:05,430
Um, well, no.

919
00:54:06,014 --> 00:54:08,517
It's just a superstition, of course.

920
00:54:08,600 --> 00:54:13,730
But believing in things like that
can still bring us comfort.

921
00:54:17,943 --> 00:54:18,944
[exhales]

922
00:54:24,616 --> 00:54:25,617
Thank you.

923
00:54:26,618 --> 00:54:29,580
Take care of yourself, Heeju.

924
00:54:41,717 --> 00:54:43,760
[Woogy] All right.
So what'd he say?

925
00:54:43,844 --> 00:54:46,722
[car engine rumbling]

926
00:54:46,805 --> 00:54:49,766
[engine revving]

927
00:54:56,565 --> 00:54:57,733
[Woogy] By the way.

928
00:54:59,276 --> 00:55:02,279
Heeju, do you have to go this far?

929
00:55:02,362 --> 00:55:03,822
Just for Lee Dokyung?

930
00:55:04,906 --> 00:55:06,783
I mean, you're helping with his travel.

931
00:55:08,493 --> 00:55:10,287
And giving him half
of the gold bars, too.

932
00:55:13,790 --> 00:55:16,543
I just, I overheard you talking on
the phone yesterday.

933
00:55:17,502 --> 00:55:19,212
It's not like I meant to.

934
00:55:19,463 --> 00:55:21,340
It was an accident!
It was.

935
00:55:21,423 --> 00:55:23,925
I went back to grab something I left
and I heard you.

936
00:55:24,009 --> 00:55:26,094
It really, really was an accident.

937
00:55:30,641 --> 00:55:32,184
It was his to begin with.

938
00:55:32,893 --> 00:55:35,354
I figured I should give him his share.

939
00:55:35,437 --> 00:55:37,648
Lee Dokyung's share
is half of the bars?

940
00:55:37,731 --> 00:55:39,066
[Woogy scoffs]
Really?

941
00:55:39,650 --> 00:55:41,026
Heeju, do you-

942
00:55:41,109 --> 00:55:42,653
do you still love that asshole?

943
00:55:43,195 --> 00:55:45,739
Huh? Even after everything he did to you?

944
00:55:45,822 --> 00:55:47,324
Didn't you break up already?

945
00:55:48,492 --> 00:55:49,618
Yeah, we did.

946
00:55:53,163 --> 00:55:54,373
We're breaking up.

947
00:55:55,540 --> 00:55:58,126
But it's not like I want him
to be unhappy.

948
00:55:58,210 --> 00:55:59,795
What does that even mean?

949
00:56:01,046 --> 00:56:02,964
Ugh, I don't know.
Leave me alone.

950
00:56:03,048 --> 00:56:04,216
It's my gold anyway.

951
00:56:04,299 --> 00:56:05,509
No, it's mine, too!

952
00:56:06,551 --> 00:56:09,221
Of those 100 gold bars,
5% belongs to me.

953
00:56:10,597 --> 00:56:12,391
You're just gonna give half to Dokyung?

954
00:56:12,474 --> 00:56:13,475
Okay, then.

955
00:56:13,934 --> 00:56:15,769
You can have 10% of my share.

956
00:56:16,353 --> 00:56:19,856
For every ten-kilo gold bar I cash in,
you get a one-kilo bar.

957
00:56:20,148 --> 00:56:21,149
Sound good?

958
00:56:24,444 --> 00:56:25,445
[inhales sharply]

959
00:56:25,529 --> 00:56:27,489
Wait a minute.
Let me just do the math.

960
00:56:28,115 --> 00:56:29,741
Four, five, six, seven.

961
00:56:30,784 --> 00:56:32,661
[gasps]
Ten billion?

962
00:56:34,663 --> 00:56:35,747
I get ten billion?

963
00:56:39,793 --> 00:56:43,630
Wow! Ten bill! Fuck me!

964
00:56:44,172 --> 00:56:45,882
[Heeju] Is that enough for you?

965
00:56:46,383 --> 00:56:47,843
That's all you've ever wanted?
STYLE
::cue()

966
00:56:49,261 --> 00:56:51,096
Why?

967
00:56:52,889 --> 00:56:54,266
[Woogy] Will you give me more if I ask?

968
00:56:56,601 --> 00:56:58,186
No, I was just wondering.

969
00:56:58,770 --> 00:57:00,397
You'd do anything for money.

970
00:57:00,856 --> 00:57:02,607
Yet you've been the least greedy.

971
00:57:04,151 --> 00:57:08,155
Every other person around me has tried
to steal everything I had.

972
00:57:09,489 --> 00:57:11,908
Really? Huh.
I, uh, never thought about it.

973
00:57:16,496 --> 00:57:19,499
[motorcycle engine rumbling]

974
00:57:21,334 --> 00:57:22,711
[brakes squeaking]

975
00:57:32,596 --> 00:57:34,723
[Delivery Man] Hi, good evening.
Did you order express delivery?

976
00:57:34,806 --> 00:57:35,807
Yeah.

977
00:57:35,891 --> 00:57:36,933
[Delivery Man] Okay.

978
00:57:40,687 --> 00:57:43,690
[♪ tense music]

979
00:58:00,165 --> 00:58:02,167
[car engine revving]

980
00:58:08,965 --> 00:58:11,426
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

981
00:58:11,510 --> 00:58:14,513
[phone ringing]

982
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:27,025
[phone trilling]

983
00:58:27,108 --> 00:58:28,109
[phone chimes]

984
00:58:44,668 --> 00:58:47,671
[gate rattling]

985
00:58:52,425 --> 00:58:55,303
[door clanging]

986
00:58:55,387 --> 00:58:56,388
Fuck.

987
00:59:05,647 --> 00:59:08,650
[creaking]

988
00:59:15,949 --> 00:59:16,950
[snaps]

989
00:59:17,033 --> 00:59:20,036
[door creaking]

990
00:59:22,998 --> 00:59:24,499
[creaking]

991
00:59:25,333 --> 00:59:26,334
[lock clicks]

992
00:59:46,646 --> 00:59:49,649
[metal detector clicking]

993
00:59:52,986 --> 00:59:55,989
[metal detector beeping]

994
01:00:04,623 --> 01:00:05,624
[light clicks on]

995
01:00:06,583 --> 01:00:07,584
Why are you here?

996
01:00:08,752 --> 01:00:09,794
H-Heeju.

997
01:00:10,462 --> 01:00:11,504
[gun cocks]

998
01:00:12,172 --> 01:00:14,841
[♪ suspenseful music]
STYLE
::cue()

999
01:00:38,490 --> 01:00:41,493
[♪ music continues]

1000
01:01:00,637 --> 01:01:03,640
[♪ dramatic music]

1001
01:01:10,772 --> 01:01:15,402
[Male Singer] ♪ Another day another hour ♪

1002
01:01:15,485 --> 01:01:19,781
♪ Free falling in my mind ♪

1003
01:01:19,864 --> 01:01:26,871
♪ I will find all of the reasons
for leaving ♪

1004
01:01:29,207 --> 01:01:34,295
♪ When everyone around me's changing ♪

1005
01:01:34,379 --> 01:01:38,758
♪ Everyone but me ♪

1006
01:01:38,842 --> 01:01:43,179
♪ All the things I thought I could be ♪

1007
01:01:44,264 --> 01:01:46,725
♪ Are out of reach ♪

1008
01:01:48,643 --> 01:01:53,231
♪ I leave it all behind ♪

1009
01:01:53,314 --> 01:01:57,277
♪ As you fall in line ♪

1010
01:01:57,360 --> 01:02:01,865
♪ I'm not expecting any light
at your door ♪

1011
01:02:01,948 --> 01:02:03,616
♪ There's nothing left ♪

1012
01:02:03,700 --> 01:02:09,956
♪ Just the pieces of everything
we could have been before ♪

1013
01:02:10,040 --> 01:02:14,252
♪ Evermore ♪

1014
01:02:14,335 --> 01:02:20,175
♪ I don't feel it like I used to ♪

1015
01:02:20,258 --> 01:02:22,510
♪ Anymore ♪

1016
01:02:35,148 --> 01:02:39,736
♪ You could find me in the dark ♪

1017
01:02:39,819 --> 01:02:44,032
♪ Still calling through the night ♪

1018
01:02:44,115 --> 01:02:48,995
♪ I leave behind all of the seasons ♪

1019
01:02:49,079 --> 01:02:51,748
♪ I've dreamed of ♪

1020
01:02:54,125 --> 01:03:01,049
♪ But the water's rising over
everything I've known ♪

1021
01:03:01,132 --> 01:03:07,138
♪ Drifting out here all alone ♪

1022
01:03:08,765 --> 01:03:12,852
♪ On your own ♪

1023
01:03:12,936 --> 01:03:17,482
♪ So leave it all behind ♪

1024
01:03:17,565 --> 01:03:21,945
♪ As you fall in line ♪

1025
01:03:22,028 --> 01:03:26,324
♪ I'm not expecting any light
at your door ♪

1026
01:03:26,407 --> 01:03:27,992
♪ There's nothing left ♪

1027
01:03:28,076 --> 01:03:34,207
♪ Just the pieces of everything
we could have been before ♪

1028
01:03:34,290 --> 01:03:38,586
♪ Evermore ♪

1029
01:03:38,670 --> 01:03:41,214
♪ I don't... ♪
